# Address Book Application

## Overview
This is an Address Book Application developed using Spring Boot. It allows users to manage their contacts and keep track of changes made to them.

## Features
- Add, update, and delete contacts.
- Retrieve all contacts or a specific contact by ID.
- Track changes made to contacts.

## How to Run
1. Ensure you have Java 8 or higher installed.
2. Clone the repository.
3. Navigate to the project directory and run the application using the command `./mvnw spring-boot:run`.

## API Endpoints
- `GET /api/contacts`: Retrieve all contacts.
- `GET /api/contacts/{id}`: Retrieve a specific contact by ID.
- `POST /api/contacts`: Add a new contact.
- `PUT /api/contacts/{id}`: Update a specific contact.
- `DELETE /api/contacts/{id}`: Delete a specific contact.
- `GET /history/contacts`: Retrieve contact history.

## Database
The application uses an in-memory H2 database. The console is accessible at `http://localhost:8080/h2-console`.

